sshpass -p "$SV_PASS" scp -o UserKnownHostsFile=/dev/null -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no ./file/path/*.js $SV_USER@$IP:/path/to/copy

============SSH to VM C from VM A via VM B=========
Incase if we a are using jumphost to connect to VM C, top copy files directly from VM C to VM A (via VM B) use this command

# Start the agent
eval "$(ssh-agent)"

# Add both keys
ssh-add ~/.ssh/key_for_vm_b
ssh-add ~/.ssh/key_for_vm_c (Both the ssh keys should be on the source VM, just copy it to here from VM B which is a jump host)

# Then run:
scp -o ProxyJump=user_b@vm_b user_c@vm_c:/path/to/file /path/to/local/

